# SEO & GEO

Kompservisas depends on organic traffic from both classic search engines (Google,
Bing) and generative engines (ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews, Gemini).
Optimize for both.

## Per-Page Metadata

- Every page renders `<PageHead name={Pages.X.name} isProductPage={false} />`.
  It reads titles, descriptions, keywords, canonical URL, and OG tags from
  `STATIC_METADATA[locale][name]` in `src/metaData.ts`.
- When adding a page, add a matching entry to `STATIC_METADATA` for **both** `lt` and `en`.
- Canonical URL format: `https://kompservisas.lt${path}` (locale-prefixed for `en`).
- Use **one** `<h1>` per page; keep heading hierarchy (`h1` → `h2` → `h3`) semantic.

## Structured Data (JSON-LD)

- Product pages: `<ProductJsonLd>` from `next-seo` with `availability`
  (`InStock` / `OutOfStock`), `itemCondition` (`UsedCondition`), `price`,
  `priceCurrency: "EUR"`, and real `images`.
- Add `BreadcrumbJsonLd` anywhere `BreadcrumbList` is rendered.
- Consider `OrganizationJsonLd` / `LocalBusinessJsonLd` once in the root layout
  (physical shop address, phone, opening hours).
- Add `FAQPageJsonLd` for pages with Q&A content.

## Rendering

- Always render primary content via ISR (`getStaticProps` + `revalidate: ISR_REVALIDATE_SECONDS`).
  Client-only content is invisible to most crawlers and generative engines.
- Use semantic HTML: `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, `<section>`, `<aside>`.
- Every `<Image>` needs a descriptive `alt` (brand, model, condition — not "image1").

## GEO (Generative Engine Optimization)

Generative engines extract facts and cite sources. Make extraction easy:

- **Entity-rich text**: mention brand, model number, CPU, RAM, grade, and price
  in plain text, not only in images or image alt.
- **Concise factual paragraphs**: short sentences with concrete specs beat
  marketing prose.
- **Explicit answers**: where users ask questions (warranty, delivery, condition
  grading), provide a direct answer paragraph near the top of the section.
- **Consistent naming**: use the same entity names across pages (e.g. "ThinkPad T14 Gen 3")
  so engines can link mentions.
- **Linked sources of truth**: cross-link related pages (product ↔ category ↔ FAQ).
- **Fresh dates**: include last-updated dates on articles/FAQs where relevant.

## Don't

- Don't use client-only rendering for primary product/category content.
- Don't ship pages without metadata entries in both locales.
- Don't stuff keywords — write for humans; engines reward clarity.
